A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor vehicles and
2 traffic, so as to provide for the operation of miniature on-road vehicles on certain highways;
3 to provide for standards for registration of such vehicles; to provide for issuance of license
4 plates for miniature on-road vehicles; to provide for an annual licensing fee for such vehicles;
5 to provide for issuance of certificates of title by the Department of Revenue for such
6 vehicles; to provide for equipment and operating standards for such vehicles; to provide local
7 authorities with the power to prohibit operation of miniature on-road vehicles; to require
8 posting of notice of such prohibition upon highways; to revise and provide for a definition;
9 to provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and
10 for other purposes.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
12 SECTION 1.
13 Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor vehicles and traffic, is
14 amended in Code Section 40-1-1, relating to definitions, by revising paragraph (27.1) and
15 adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
H. B. 308
- 1 -

25 LC 39 4568
16 "(27.1) 'Miniature on-road vehicle' means any motorized vehicle designed and
17 manufactured for use upon roadways in another country that has been imported into the
18 United States with a valid certificate of title or registration from the exporting country
19 and in compliance with all federal importation requirements and which has the following
20 characteristics:
21 (A) Has the capability to transport persons;
22 (B) Operates between 25 miles per hour (40.2 kilometers per hour) and 65 miles per
23 hour (104.6 kilometers per hour);
24 (C) Has an overall width of 80 inches (2,030 millimeters) or less, exclusive of
25 accessories or attachments;
26 (D) Is designed to travel on four or more wheels;
27 (E) Uses a steering wheel for steering control;
28 (F) Contains a nonstraddle seat;
29 (G) Has a gross vehicle weight rating of less than 4,000 pounds (1,814 kilograms); and
30 (H) Is not designed or manufactured as a golf cart, all-terrain vehicle, or multipurpose
31 off-highway vehicle.
32 (27.2) 'Minimal risk condition' means a low-risk operating mode in which a fully
33 autonomous vehicle operating without a human driver achieves a reasonably safe state,
34 such as bringing the vehicle to a complete stop, upon experiencing a failure of the
35 vehicle's automated driving system that renders the vehicle unable to perform the entire
36 dynamic driving task."
